ainly have our eyes on during this 2024 election cycle. - Angela Johnson Read More Why White Fear Of Black Power Outlawed An African American Holiday Before Juneteenth Long before Juneteenth, enslaved and free Black New Yorkers celebrated African culture during a holiday that eventually made white people feel threatened. - Nigel Roberts Read More Angel Reese Speak on Having Enough of The Caitlin Clark Comparisons There are 144 players in the WNBA. Based on how mainstream media has covered the league this season, you\u2019d think there\u2019s only one. Yes, I\u2019m talking about Caitlin Clark. The rookie phenom\u2019s unprecedented popularity has brought a lot of new fans to the game. Unfortunately, with all those new fans comes uninformed BS. - Stephanie Holland Read More Peek Inside NY Yankee Derek Jeter\u2019s $15 Million Castle That Just Sold After being on the market for nearly six years, Derek Jeter\u2019s Orange County property has entered contract. However, the price that was paid for it as well as who bought the home remain unknown. - Candace McDuffie Read More Homeless New Orleans Black Teen Graduates as Valedictorian, And His Story Will Melt Your Heart A 19-year-old New Orleans student just proved that with hard work and determination, you can overcome almost any obstacle. Elijah Hogan graduated as one of two valedictorians of the class of 2024 at Walter L. Cohen High School. Hogan, who leaves Cohen with a 3.93 GPA and a college scholarship, did it all while living in a homeless shelter. - Angela Johnson Read More How a Florida Driver is Alive Because of These Two Black 14-year-old Boys A Florida driver lost control of his pickup truck and swerved into a canal last week. However, by the time sheriff\u2019s deputies arrived to the scene of the crash, they found the driver had already been rescued. - Kalyn Womack Read More Brawls and All: Here\u2019s The Most Ridiculous Spirit Airlines Moments Over the Years The Internet Loves Spirit Airlines because cray c